System.Data.Common contains classes shared by the .NET Framework data providers.

A .NET Framework data provider describes a collection of classes used to access
a data source, such as a database, in the managed space. Supported providers
include the .NET Framework Data Provider for ODBC, the .NET Framework Data
Provider for OLEDB, the .NET Framework Data Provider for Oracle, and the .NET
Framework Data Provider for SQL Server. The classes in System.Data.Common are
intended to give developers a way to write ADO.NET code that will work against
all .NET Framework data providers.

